For a better understanding of the present invention and in order to show how the same may be carried into effect reference will now be made, by way of example, to the accompanying drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 illustrates a simple current mirror of known design;


FIG. 2 illustrates a simple 4-bit digital to analogue converter of known design;


FIG. 3 illustrates the geometrical chip layout for the digital to analogue converter of FIG. 2 according to the common-centroid method;


FIG. 4 illustrates a current mirror incorporating a calibration system;


FIG. 5 illustrates in more detail gate connections to a mirroring transistor of the current mirror of FIG. 4;


FIG. 6 illustrates the calibration system of FIG. 4 applied to a digital to analogue converter of the type shown in FIG. 2;


FIG. 7 illustrates a modification to the calibration system of FIG. 6; and


FIG. 8 illustrates the calibration circuit of FIG. 4 applied to a differential amplifier.
